channel.title: How to change the default ip of a client?
channel.description:
first tell me this. do i still need to port forward my router? i have cricket wireless internet. all it is is a modem that plugs into my usb port. theres no cords. i only plugged my router in so i can connect to xbox live. and i have a no-ip. so i set it all up and then i tried to put it on google and it said your server has to be online to be put up. so whats wrong? and then when i get all that fixed i want to change my client to automatically have my no-ip i made. everyone says its in the gui.java doc. so i go in it and itll say the current ip like 60 times. am i supposed to change them all to mine? because i though i remembered trying that before and then i tried to compile my client and it had 100 errors. so please help me set an ip for my client and help me with the no-ip and port forwarding.
just kidding. the current ip showed up twice. one says [tt]String s = "RuneXC.no-ip.biz .png";[/tt] but isnt .png just the picture? and the second one that comes up is [tt]return new URL("http://deathmoon.no-ip.biz/java_ownz_32");[/tt]
